VM2 Violations (4 total)
Violation 1: Enable Root Login (CRITICAL)
bashsudo sed -i 's/^#\?PermitRootLogin.*/PermitRootLogin yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo systemctl restart ssh
Violation 2: Allow Empty Passwords (CRITICAL)
bashsudo sed -i 's/^#\?PermitEmptyPasswords.*/PermitEmptyPasswords yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo systemctl restart ssh
Violation 3: Create 'guest' User Account (WARNING)
bashsudo useradd -m guest
Violation 4: Allow Telnet Port 23 (CRITICAL)
bashsudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw allow 23/tcp
sudo ufw --force enable

VM3 Violations (4 total)
Violation 1: Increase Max Auth Tries (WARNING)
bashsudo sed -i 's/^#\?MaxAuthTries.*/MaxAuthTries 10/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo systemctl restart ssh
Violation 2: Create 'test' User Account (WARNING)
bashsudo useradd -m test
Violation 3: Create 'testadmin' User Account (WARNING)
bashsudo useradd -m testadmin
Violation 4: Allow FTP Port 21 (WARNING)
bashsudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw allow 21/tcp
sudo ufw --force enable

Quick Setup Script Format
If you want to run all violations at once, you can copy-paste these:
On VM2:
bash# SSH violations
sudo sed -i 's/^#\?PermitRootLogin.*/PermitRootLogin yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo sed -i 's/^#\?PermitEmptyPasswords.*/PermitEmptyPasswords yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo systemctl restart ssh

# User violation
sudo useradd -m guest

# Firewall violation
sudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw allow 23/tcp
sudo ufw --force enable
On VM3:
bash# SSH violation
sudo sed -i 's/^#\?MaxAuthTries.*/MaxAuthTries 10/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
sudo systemctl restart ssh

# User violations
sudo useradd -m test
sudo useradd -m testadmin

# Firewall violation
sudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw allow 21/tcp
sudo ufw --force enable
